    <description>DBACW is an expansion for the WRG De Bellis Antiquitatis rules version 2.0 adapting the DBA mechanics to the American Civil War.  Ownership of the DBA rules are required.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;While the system is designed as an expansion to DBA, there are grades for troop types (&amp;quot;Veteran&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Experience&amp;quot;, and &amp;quot;Raw&amp;quot;) and Generals (&amp;quot;Good&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Average&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Poor&amp;quot;), which is more similar to De Bellis Multitudinus (DBM).  A typical army is a division composed of multiple brigades (each of which has its own commander).  Rules are also given for larger battles forming Corps sized units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scale:&amp;#10;Infantry element:  4-500 men&amp;#10;Cavalry element:  3-400 men&amp;#10;Artillery element:  8-12 guns&amp;#10;Ground scale:  1&amp;quot; = 100 paces (about 80 yards)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
